Governor Chukwuma Charles Soludo of Anambra State has visited the Ekwulobia Prisons where he inspected the facility. The governor at the end of the inspection promised that a new system will be put in place.
Soludo on his official twitter handle @ccsoludo stated: “Yesterday, I visited Ekwulobia Prison after my thanksgiving mass.
“During my visit, I walked around the prison facility to see its present condition and I had a chat with the prisoners and the wardens and I assured them there will be a new system that will be set up.”
Governor Soludo had on his inauguration declared that there is no time for festivities, saying he will go to work immediately.
